post_text: Family Appreciation Week (June 8-12) is designed to show our deepest appreciation for your continued partnership in your child/ren’s education. We have always known families play a vital role in the education of our students, as you love, nurture, protect, teach, provide for, and serve as role models for our students. Strong families, such as yours, provide much-needed support and guidance to ensure our students succeed as learners and members of a global community. #FamilyAppreciationWeek2020

post_text:
Are you wondering how you can support your child's natural inquiry at home? Inquiry is all around us! Try one of these to grow and learn together at home!

Nature Walks: When you are out on your daily walks, look for the signs of Spring. Look, talk, draw, and inquire about the plants and animals springing to life!

Family Game Night: Games are a great way to build life skills, or "approaches to learning." Sitting down as a family, taking turns, solving problems, and playing helps students develop the skills they need to work cooperatively in an academic setting and relate to others!

post_text: Today’s activity for Mental Health Awareness month invites you to try an exercise in positive self-talk and managing your inner critic – the voice inside your head that puts you down and says mean and negative things. It is very easy to get bogged down with negative thinking and talking badly about ourselves, especially in times of high stress. Think about what your inner critic might look like. Is it a magical creature, a person, an animal, a cartoon, or something else completely? Take some time to draw your inner critic (it doesn’t have to look perfect and amazing, just something that represents the idea you have in your head).

In recognition of Mental Health Awareness month, The Children’s Guild Alliance Outpatient Mental Health Clinic has created activities and tips that will help us all care for our mental wellness. We are all trying to make our way through these unusual circumstances and hope that these strategies can help bring some positivity and peace into your day!

In today’s activity, you will use the skills you learned yesterday regarding mindfulness and be invited to connect with your physical self and nature. We hope you find time in your day to try it out!

post_text: THE CHALLENGE: 1,500 CHROMEBOOKS NEEDED FOR OUR STUDENTS IN THE NEXT TWO WEEKS. The Maryland and DC school closures have posed unique problems for our students. Many of our students lack devices and Internet connectivity to access online learning while their schools are closed. The Children’s Guild Alliance is committed in this crucial time to give our students the needed resources to continue their education. Help us purchase 1,500 Chromebooks in the next two weeks. $250 puts a Chromebook in a child’s hands and $50 buys a WiFi hotspot for a family without Internet. $5,000 buys a classroom set of Chromebooks for students. Support our kids and donate today: https://kidsfirstamerica.org/chromebooks/
